craterdog.collections.abstractions

Class OrderedCollection<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • craterdog.smart.SmartObject<Collection<E>>
      • craterdog.collections.abstractions.Collection<E>
        • craterdog.collections.abstractions.OpenCollection<E>
          • craterdog.collections.abstractions.OrderedCollection<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of element managed by this collection.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Accessible<E>, Dynamic<E>, Ordered<E>, Sequential<E>, java.lang.Comparable<Collection<E>>, java.lang.Iterable<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Bag, Set

    public abstract class OrderedCollection<E>
extends OpenCollection<E>
implements Ordered<E>
    This abstract class defines the invariant methods that all ordered collections must inherit. An ordered collection automatically orders its elements based on the comparison function implemented by a specified Comparator. If no comparator is specified, the elements extend the Comparable interface.
    Author:
    Derk Norton
